        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 1:51PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Frenchman Lake, or 8 miles east of Beckwourth, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beckwourth, Frenchman Lake, Grizzly Campground, Lake Davis, Big Cove
Campground, Chilcoot Campground, Frenchman Campground, Spring Creek
Campground, and Beckwourth-Nervino Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
